 Catholic Academy,\"] ''The Rambler'' (1861).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/ns2a634760406londuoft#page/n7/mode/2up \"D\u00f6llinger on the Temporal Power,\"] ''The Rambler'' (1861).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/ns2a634760406londuoft#page/190/mode/2up \"Mr. Goldwin Smith's Irish History,\"] ''The Rambler'' (1862). \n* [https://archive.org/stream/ns2a634760406londuoft#page/318/mode/2up \"The Protestant Theory of Persecution,\"] ''The Rambler'' (1862).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/ra634742501londuoft#page/n9/mode/2up \"Nationality,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1862). \n* [https://archive.org/stream/ra634742501londuoft#page/146/mode/2up \"Secret History of Charles II,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1862). \n* [https://archive.org/stream/a634742502londuoft#page/152/mode/2up \"Confessions of Frederick the Great,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1863).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/a634742502londuoft#page/504/mode/2up \"The Waldensian Forgeries,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1863).\n* [https://archive.org/stream/aa634742502londuoft#page/162/mode/2up \"Ultramontanism,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1863). \n* [https://archive.org/stream/aa634742502londuoft#page/610/mode/2up \"Medi\u00e6val Fables of the Popes,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1863). \n* [https://archive.org/stream/a634742500londuoft#page/208/mode/2up \"The Munich Congress,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1864). \n* [https://archive.org/stream/a634742500londuoft#page/666/mode/2up \"Conflicts with Rome,\"] ''Home and Foreign Review'' (1864).\n* \"Material Resources of the Papacy,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"Fra Paolo Sarpi,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867). \n* \"The Case of Monte Cassino,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867). \n* \"D\u00f6llinger on Universities,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867). \n* \"The Ministerial Changes in Italy,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867). \n* \"Secret History of the Italian Crisis,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"The Secret Bull,\" ''The Chronicle'' (1867).\n* \"Reminiscences of Massimo d