{"title_page": "Hussain Faisal", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=February 2019}}\n{{COI|date=June 2017}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Hssaf.jpg|thumb]]\n'''Hussain Faisal''' is an [[Islamic]] professional reciter, music producer and composer from the [[Kingdom of Bahrain|Bahrain]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/document/351437923/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9|title=\u0627\u0644\u0628\u064a\u0648\u062a\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0645\u0631\u064a\u0629|last=page 14|website=Scribd|language=en|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref> He was born in the city of [[Bani Jamra]], Bahrain<ref name=\":0\" /> where he grew up with his 2 brothers and 2 sisters until his late twenties'''<ref name=\":0\" />'''. At that time, he studied and finished his high school then went to the [[University of Bahrain]] where he received his bachelor degree in BIS (Business Information Systems). Then he started his Music Production and arrangement career focusing on the Islamic music productions mainly and Arabic in general with some vocal coaching from time to time. He started his Islamic professional singing (reciting) career in the early 2000s. In 2014, in the month of [[Muharram]], his album (Ard Anishdak)<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://shiavoice.com/cat-8994|title=\u0631\u0648\u0627\u062f\u064a\u062f \u0622\u062e\u0631\u0648\u0646 \u2013 \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|last=Shiavoice|website=shiavoice.com|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.alhoja.net/mediaa/showcat-840-0.html|title=\u0634\u0628\u0643\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u062d\u062c\u0629|website=alhoja.net|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref> gained multiple millions of views to his video clips on his YouTube channel.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCoh6UUUq_vhX403HSCKgCHA|title=Hussain Faisal {{!}} \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref> He is one of very few Islamic singers whose YouTube channels have been legitimately \"Verified\" by The YouTube Copyright community<ref name=\":3\" /> and his copyrights are managed by Bint-Alhuda media company in [[Lebanon]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bintelhuda.com/|title=Bintelhuda {{!}} \u0628\u0646\u062a \u0627\u0644\u0647\u062f\u0649|website=bintelhuda.com|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref> He's well known for his recent 3 Albums<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" /> and his songs (latmiyat) had a fair opportunity to be viewed on various Islamic TV Channels<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.alkawthartv.com/news/71453|title=\u0642\u0635\u064a\u062f\u0629 \u0631\u0627\u0626\u0639\u0629 \u0639\u0627\u0634\u0642 \u0641\u0627\u0637\u0645\u0629 \u2013  \u0644\u0644\u0631\u0627\u062f\u0648\u062f \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|website=alkawthartv.com {{!}} \u0642\u0646\u0627\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u06a9\u0648\u062b\u0631|language=ar|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref><ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://arabic.irib.ir/news/item/420/151696/483/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%AF%D8%B3-%D8%B9%D8%B4%D9%82-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%AF-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%8A%D9%86-%D9%81%D9%8A%D8%B5%D9%84.html|title=\u0627\u0644\u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0627\u0642\u062f\u0633 \u0639\u0634\u0642 \u0644\u0644\u0631\u0627\u062f\u0648\u062f \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|website=arabic.irib.ir|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref> and aired on few Islamic radio broadcasts<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":4\" /> as well. He has recited in [[Bahrain]],<ref>{{Citation|last=Hussain Faisal {{!}} \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|title=\u0644\u064a\u0634 \u0639\u0627\u064a\u0641 \u062e\u064a\u0645\u062a\u0643 {{!}} \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|date=2016-11-09|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y13PZin71VA|accessdate=2017-06-16}}</ref> [[Oman]], [[Saudi Arabia]], [[Iraq]], [[London]],<ref>{{Citation|last=Al-Akbar Foundation|title=\u0645\u0627\u062a\u062a \u0641\u0627\u0637\u0645\u0629 \u2013 \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|date=2016-03-08|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=nvoA1dvvCos|accessdate=2017-06-16}}</ref> [[Lebanon]] and [[Iran]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Faisal, Hussain}}\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Bahraini singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=February 2019}}\n{{COI|date=June 2017}}\n}}\n\n[[File:Hssaf.jpg|thumb]]\n'''Hussain Faisal''' is an [[Islamic]] professional reciter, music producer and composer from the [[Kingdom of Bahrain|Bahrain]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/document/351437923/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D9%8A%D9%88%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%AA-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%A9|title=\u0627\u0644\u0628\u064a\u0648\u062a\u0627\u062a \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0645\u0631\u064a\u0629|last=page 14|website=Scribd|language=en|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref> He was born in the city of [[Bani Jamra]], Bahrain<ref name=\":0\" /> where he grew up with his 2 brothers and 2 sisters until his late twenties'''<ref name=\":0\" />'''. At that time, he studied and finished his high school then went to the [[University of Bahrain]] where he received his bachelor degree in BIS (Business Information Systems). Then he started his Music Production and arrangement career focusing on the Islamic music productions mainly and Arabic in general with some vocal coaching from time to time. He started his Islamic professional singing (reciting) career at the Early 2000's. In 2014, in the month of [[Muharram]], his album (Ard Anishdak)<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://shiavoice.com/cat-8994|title=\u0631\u0648\u0627\u062f\u064a\u062f \u0622\u062e\u0631\u0648\u0646 \u2013 \u062d\u0633\u064a\u0646 \u0641\u064a\u0635\u0644|last=Shiavoice|website=shiavoice.com|access-date=2017-06-16}}</ref><ref n